In a small bowl, mix together yogurt, mayonnaise, chutney, curry powder, and cayenne to taste. If grapes are larger than 3/4 inch, cut in half. In a large bowl, mix grapes, chicken, celery, green onions, and yogurt mixture. Add salt to taste. Cut melon in half lengthwise; scoop out and discard seeds. Cut halves in half lengthwise. Set each melon quarter on a dinner plate. Spoon 1/4 of the chicken salad into each melon cavity, letting it spill over sides. Sprinkle equally with pistachios and mint.